-94.56 -11.52  TD -0.0796  Tc 1.213  Tw (In considering this episode of David\222s life, we see both the tragedy of his moral failure and the ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.061  Tc 0.7182  Tw (power of God\222s forgiveness. David sees himself in a different light; he is a warrior for whom to be afraid  ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0785  Tc 0.4385  Tw (would be the greatest defea) Tj109.92 0  TD -0.0963  Tc 0.4281  Tw (t. It is interesting to observe that a person rarely sees himself as he really is. The ) Tj-109.92 -11.52  TD -0.0537  Tc 0.1737  Tw (real problems will come to the surface from time to time, as we see in David\222s reaction to Absalom\222s death, ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0719  Tc 0.5119  Tw (but they are not a conscious part of daily life. Man doesn\222t ) Tj240.48 0  TD -0.0993  Tc 0.4113  Tw (know himself as he really is. David seems to be ) Tj-240.48 -11.52  TD -0.074  Tc 0.514  Tw (more concerned about the fact that people could take him for a coward than anything else. David\222s attitude ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0768  Tc 0.3834  Tw (may also indicate that he endeavors to find his balance on the emotional level of his life, after hav) Tj393.6 0  TD -0.0499  Tc -0.0701  Tw (ing found ) Tj-393.6 -11.04  TD -0.0619  Tc 0.4219  Tw (it on the spiritual level. He knows that God has forgiven him, but emotionally he has trouble accepting this ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1022  Tc 0.7593  Tw (fact. David was not a coward by nature; yet when he realized that there was an absolute absence of fear in ) TjT* -0.0698  Tc 0.9098  Tw (his heart under these circumst) Tj121.92 0  TD -0.0565  Tc 0.6565  Tw (ances, he considered this to be the result of God\222s supernatural intervention. ) Tj-121.92 -11.52  TD -0.0971  Tc 1.1657  Tw (When David said: \223I will not fear the tens of thousands drawn up against me on every side,\224 he was not ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0696  Tc 3.5896  Tw (bragging, but was amazed that God could bring about this quiet feeling in) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj340.8 0  TD -0.0922  Tc 3.3322  Tw (his heart under these) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-340.8 -11.52  TD -0.0759  Tc -0.0441  Tw (circumstances. ) Tj60.96 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-24.96 -11.52  TD -0.1232  Tc 1.1552  Tw (II Sam. 18 describes the battle between David\222s army and Absalom\222s. This third psalm describes ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0699  Tc 0.9857  Tw (the spiritual breakthrough in this battle. Wars on earth are shadows of the struggle that takes place in the ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1067  Tc 0.9467  Tw (heavenlies. Vi) Tj57.12 0  TD -0.0915  Tc 0.6774  Tw (ctory over the devil was won when David made a profession of faith in God. David\222s prayer ) Tj-57.12 -11.52  TD -0.129  Tc 1.0833  Tw (had been: \223Arise, O LORD! Deliver me, O my God! Strike all my enemies on the jaw; break the teeth of ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0963  Tc -0.0237  Tw (the wicked.\224 The Lord arose and struck all his enemies on the jaw) Tj259.68 0  TD -0.0974  Tc -0.0226  Tw ( and broke the teeth of the wicked. ) Tj138.24 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-361.92 -11.52  TD -0.0785  Tc 0.6252  Tw (David hoped that Absalom\222s life would be spared in this, but that was not to be. Absalom\222s death ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0676  Tc 0.4543  Tw (was, probably, the most merciful solution to the problem. The boy had grown into a mature criminal. After ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0791  Tc 1.8791  Tw (the murder of hi) Tj70.08 0  TD -0.1009  Tc 1.4529  Tw (s brother, the conspiracy against his father and the adultery with his father\222s wives and ) Tj-70.08 -11.52  TD -0.063  Tc 0.3383  Tw (concubines, there would have been no hope for a restoration of relationships. Absalom knew nothing of the ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0571  Tc 0.76  Tw (transparent fellowship with God, that was characteristic for) Tj240.96 0  TD -0.1108  Tc 0.4272  Tw ( his father. He was caught deeply in the net that ) Tj-240.96 -11.52  TD -0.1105  Tc 1.582  Tw (Satan had spread for him, and when he died, the devil received what was his already. For this purpose, ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0828  Tc -0.0372  Tw (Satan used as an instrument of death a man who had no scruples: Joab. ) Tj281.76 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-245.76 -11.52  TD -0.1064  Tc 1.5864  Tw (David was the object of \223A Sever) Tj141.6 0  TD -0.1069  Tc 1.3069  Tw (e Mercy,\224 but he did not understand this yet. He was correct, ) Tj-177.6 -11.52  TD -0.1059  Tc 0.7765  Tw (however in stating: \223From the LORD comes deliverance. May your blessing be on your people.\224 The only ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0675  Tc -0.0525  Tw (hope for the healing of the rift that had split Israel in two was an act of divine interventi) Tj346.08 0  TD -0.04  Tc 0  Tw (on.) Tj12.48 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-358.56 -256.8  TD (                              ) Tj72 0  TD (                              ) TjET89.76 88.32 144 0.48 re fBT234.24 85.92  TD( ) Tj-144 -7.2  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tw (58) Tj6.72 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf0.0101  Tc -0.1301  Tw ( Acts 12:6) Tj41.28 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) TjETendstreamendobj61 0 obj7035 endobj62 0 obj<< /Type /Page /Parent 53 0 R /Resources << /Font << /F0 6 0 R /F1 8 0 R /F2 12 0 R /F4 22 0 R >> /ProcSet 2 0 R >> /Contents 63 0 R >> endobj63 0 obj<< /Length 64 0 R >> stream
