mself; the LORD will hear when I call to him.) Tj409.92 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-409.92 -11.52  TD 0.01  Tc -0.13  Tw (4  In your anger do not sin; when you are on your beds, search your hearts and be si) Tj348.96 0  TD 0.0509  Tc -0.1709  Tw (lent. Selah) Tj44.64 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-393.6 -11.52  TD 0.0254  Tc -0.1454  Tw (5  Offer right sacrifices and trust in the LORD.) Tj195.36 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-195.36 -11.04  TD 0.0349  Tc -0.1549  Tw (6  Many are asking, "Who can show us any good?" Let the light of your face shine upon us, O LORD.) Tj425.76 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-425.76 -11.52  TD 0.0569  Tc -0.1769  Tw (7  You have filled my heart with greater joy than when their grain and new wine abound.) Tj370.56 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-370.56 -11.52  TD 0.0648  Tc -0.1848  Tw (8  I will) Tj31.68 0  TD 0.0014  Tc -0.1214  Tw ( lie down and sleep in peace, for you alone, O LORD, make me dwell in safety.) Tj323.52 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-355.2 -11.52  TD /F0 10.08  Tf( ) Tj36 -11.52  TD -0.0587  Tc 1.3521  Tw (There is no caption above this psalm, as with the previous one, that would indicate to us what ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0886  Tc 0.8916  Tw (David\222s circumstances were when he wrote this. It is clear, however, that David wa) Tj340.8 0  TD -0.1251  Tc 0.4051  Tw (s between a rock and a ) Tj-340.8 -11.52  TD -0.0981  Tc 1.0448  Tw (hard place when he wrote this poem. The words \223distress\224 and \223shame\224 point in the direction of physical ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0565  Tc -0.0635  Tw (and emotional stress. ) Tj85.92 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-49.92 -11.52  TD -0.0578  Tc 1.3214  Tw (Most commentators suppose that the psalms 3 and 4 were written at the same occasion, that is ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0862  Tc 2.8462  Tw (David\222s fligh) Tj55.2 0  TD -0.09  Tc 2.4386  Tw (t from Absalom. There were many other occasions in David\222s life, though, in which he) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-55.2 -11.52  TD -0.0744  Tc 0.8344  Tw (experienced distress; any of these occasions could serve as the background for this psalm. It is difficult to ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0448  Tc 1.4448  Tw (reconstruct such circumstances after thirty centuries, withou) Tj248.64 0  TD -0.1118  Tc 1.3009  Tw (t a caption. We can only say that we do not ) Tj-248.64 -11.52  TD -0.0876  Tc 0  Tw (know.) Tj24.48 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj11.52 -11.52  TD -0.0801  Tc 0.6561  Tw (The subject of vs. 1 is an answer to prayer. David calls God: \223my righteous God,\224 or, as the KJV ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.088  Tc 0.7303  Tw (renders it: \223God of my righteousness.\224 The Good News Bible translates it with: \223God, my defender.\224 That ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.053  Tc 0.413  Tw (is a ) Tj17.76 0  TD -0.057  Tc 0.507  Tw (beautiful title. David recognizes God as the source of his righteousness. That is sound New Testament ) Tj-17.76 -11.52  TD -0.0568  Tc 0.7634  Tw (theology! He knows that the source of his righteousness is outside himself and that he cannot boast about ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1326  Tc 2.4126  Tw (anything within himself. This is his defense. TL) Tj204 0  TD -0.1036  Tc 2.2636  Tw (B gives the interesting paraphrase: \223O God, you have) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-204 -11.52  TD -0.0777  Tc 1.6377  Tw (declared me perfect in your eyes \205\224 It is the imputed righteousness, resulting from the death of Jesus ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0548  Tc 0.7988  Tw (Christ on the cross of Golgotha that is the basis of our prayers and of God\222s answer. David did not ) Tj409.92 0  TD -0.0794  Tc -0.0406  Tw (know ) Tj-409.92 -11.52  TD -0.07  Tc 0.55  Tw (the facts of salvation as we know them, but the Holy Spirit gave him the intuitive understanding as to how ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0811  Tc 0.6011  Tw (the relationship with God worked. In his appeal to his righteousness, he actually appealed to what God has ) TjT* -0.0573  Tc 0.8973  Tw (done for him. This brought him to the) Tj156.48 0  TD -0.0701  Tc 0.5741  Tw ( understanding that, if God performed this overwhelming miracle of ) Tj-156.48 -11.04  TD -0.0863  Tc 2.8463  Tw (his justification, His meeting David\222s lesser needs would be child\222s play. This is an Old Testament) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0588  Tc 0.722  Tw (paraphrase of what Paul would later say: \223If God is for us, who can be against us? \205 Who ) Tj376.32 0  TD -0.1332  Tc 0.1732  Tw (will bring any ) Tj-376.32 -11.52  TD -0.0629  Tc -0.0571  Tw (charge against those whom God has chosen? It is God who justifies. Who is he that condemns?\224) Tj381.12 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (59) Tj6.72 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-351.84 -11.52  TD -0.0699  Tc 1.6566  Tw (The word \223distress\224 is the translation of the Hebrew ) Tj225.6 0  TD /F2 10.08  Tf0.1589  Tc 0  Tw (tsar) Tj15.84 0  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0908  Tc 1.4108  Tw (. It means a narrow, tight place, or a ) Tj-277.44 -11.52  TD -0.0765  Tc 2.1765  Tw (condition of being crowded upon. It evokes the imag) Tj226.56 0  TD -0.0684  Tc 1.6551  Tw (e of a person who has trouble breathing because ) Tj-226.56 -11.52  TD -0.0816  Tc 0.6392  Tw (something or somebody presses upon him. We are surrounded by enough oxygen for the whole creation to ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0709  Tc 1.1349  Tw (breathe, but sometimes there are outward or inward conditions that prevent normal breathing. David was ) TjT* -0.1208  Tc 0  Tw (subj) Tj16.8 0  TD -0.0601  Tc 1.1881  Tw (ect to both kinds of limitations: his own iniquity made it hard to breathe and so did the people who ) Tj-16.8 -11.52  TD -0.097  Tc 0.553  Tw (tried to rob him of his honor and dignity. If we were always inwardly perfect and balanced, the criticism of ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0269  Tc 0.7298  Tw (others would not affect us. Jesus describes th) Tj184.8 0  TD -0.0635  Tc 0.3865  Tw (e suffering of hell as a place \223where their worm does not die, ) Tj-184.8 -11.52  TD -0.0965  Tc -0.0235  Tw (and the 