 and the microcosms. ) Tj136.32 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-136.32 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.1291  Tc 1.0651  Tw (The opening sentence contains the words: YHWH and Adoni with majesty and glory. The accent ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0564  Tc 0.7364  Tw (of the whole psalm is upon the Lord as Creator, but the nam) Tj247.68 0  TD -0.0738  Tc 0.3805  Tw (es used for God are those that make reference ) Tj-247.68 -11.52  TD -0.1048  Tc 2.7581  Tw (to Him as the One who entered into the covenant with Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, and who is the) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1085  Tc 0.5885  Tw (Almighty, who rules over all. YHWH is the \223I AM,\224 Adoni is the Lord to whom we owe obedience. When ) TjT* -0.0796  Tc 0.9196  Tw (David calls Him ) Tj71.52 0  TD -0.0812  Tc 1.0546  Tw (\223our Lord,\224 he means that the Lord ought to be obeyed by us all. \223Our Lord,\224 after all, ) Tj-71.52 -11.52  TD -0.1032  Tc 1.0523  Tw (means that He is Lord of my life and I am His servant. The Redeemer, Ruler, and Creator is one and the ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.094  Tc -0.026  Tw (same God.) Tj42.24 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-42.24 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0498  Tc 2.8098  Tw (Modern man feels lost in a hostile world; he tries to) Tj0  Tc 0.36  Tw ( ) Tj239.04 0  TD -0.1016  Tc 2.4616  Tw (conquer the space in which he lives.) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-275.04 -11.52  TD -0.1013  Tc 2.7113  Tw (Redeemed man sees the harmony between himself and the rest of creation. The difference is in our) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0459  Tc -0.0741  Tw (relationship with God. ) Tj91.68 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-91.68 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0944  Tc 0.4544  Tw (David\222s choice of words in the poem is superb. He says, not only that God\222s glory and majesty are) Tj396 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-432 -11.52  TD -0.0655  Tc 0.7455  Tw (seen in creation, but also that His Name is majestic in all the earth. He speaks about God\222s Name, that is, ) Tj0 -11.04  TD -0.0832  Tc 0.7072  Tw (His character, the essence of His being. It is the character of God that makes creation vibrate with life and ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0943  Tc 0.6943  Tw (beauty. I wrote these words, early in) Tj146.88 0  TD -0.0725  Tc 0.3983  Tw ( the morning, sitting on the front porch of a friend\222s home in Jayapura, ) Tj-146.88 -11.52  TD -0.1118  Tc 0.9975  Tw (Irian Jaya, Indonesia. From there I had a breathtaking view of the bay of the city. Just at that moment the ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0731  Tc 1.9013  Tw (sun came up. It was as if the Lord wanted to prove to me the point that the) Tj326.4 0  TD -0.0582  Tc 1.6182  Tw ( reason this view was so ) Tj-326.4 -11.52  TD -0.0974  Tc 0.9107  Tw (overwhelming was because it expressed His character and beauty. God is light, and this light breaks up in ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0615  Tc 1.6329  Tw (the prism of nature into glorious gold and deep red with purple of this sunrise.  I was given a private ) TjT* -0.0438  Tc 1.8438  Tw (demonstration of a me) Tj95.04 0  TD -0.0744  Tc 1.2744  Tw (aningful expression of God\222s character. In his book ) Tj217.44 0  TD /F2 10.08  Tf0.1267  Tc 1.1933  Tw (The Abolition of Man) Tj92.64 0  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.1376  Tc 0.9776  Tw (, C. S. ) Tj-405.12 -11.52  TD -0.0686  Tc 0.4004  Tw (Lewis says some interesting things about the observation of beauty. Beauty is not the subjective reaction of ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0689  Tc -0.0511  Tw (a man to what he sees; it is an objective expression of God\222s absol) Tj262.08 0  TD -0.0839  Tc -0.0361  Tw (ute being.) Tj38.88 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-300.96 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0937  Tc 1.442  Tw (The psalm is written from the viewpoint of a redeemed man. Nothing of what David says here ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0721  Tc 0.7749  Tw (would make any sense for a person who still lives in sin. In quoting this psalm, the writer to the Hebrews ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1149  Tc 1.4349  Tw (says: \223At present