, as long as we treat ) Tj-180 -11.52  TD -0.0308  Tc 1.0537  Tw (our neighbor decently. But unless we love God with all our heart and with all our soul and with all our ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0738  Tc 2.9367  Tw (strength, we cannot possibly love our neighbor as ourselves. It is easy to deceive ourse) Tj384 0  TD -0.0086  Tc 2.7686  Tw (lves in our) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-384 -11.52  TD -0.0785  Tc -0.0415  Tw (relationship with God. John says: \223) Tj138.72 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj5.28 0  TD -0.1062  Tc 2.1462  Tw (If anyone says, \221I love God,\222 yet hates his brother, he is a liar. For) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-144 -11.52  TD -0.0885  Tc -0.0315  Tw (anyone who does not love his brother, whom he has seen, cannot love God, whom he has not seen.\224) Tj393.6 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (178) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-403.68 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0311  Tc 1.5911  Tw (So much in way of introduction to this ) Tj170.88 0  TD -0.0908  Tc 1.2308  Tw (psalm in which David commences with the complaint: ) Tj-206.88 -11.52  TD -0.1114  Tc 0.8641  Tw (\223The godly are no more.\224 The Hebrew word for \223godly\224 is ) Tj243.84 0  TD /F2 10.08  Tf0.1433  Tc 0  Tw (hasid) Tj22.56 0  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.1136  Tc 0.5936  Tw (, which means a member of the covenant ) Tj-266.4 -11.52  TD -0.087  Tc 2.911  Tw (people. Godly people are always rare; the crowd always follows evil. This becomes obvious in the) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0186  Tc 0  Tw (deterior) Tj31.2 0  TD -0.0632  Tc -0.0568  Tw (ation of human relations. God lives where there is love among brethren.) Tj284.64 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-315.84 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0778  Tc 3.1806  Tw (By uttering this complaint, David places himself with the godly. His complaint is also an) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0792  Tc 1.0792  Tw (indication of his feeling of loneliness. Being a social creature, man needs the company of hi) Tj379.68 0  TD -0.0539  Tc 0.4139  Tw (s fellowmen. ) Tj-379.68 -11.52  TD -0.057  Tc 0.273  Tw (Fellowship with God is, of course, the most important and fundamental thing in life. But, even if a man has ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0651  Tc 1.1984  Tw (intimate fellowship with God, he needs intercourse with other people in order to live a healthy and well ) TjT* -0.0842  Tc 0.7322  Tw (balanced life. God intends it ) Tj118.56 0  TD -0.0671  Tc 0.8171  Tw (to be so that we are reached by God\222s love through the lives of other people ) Tj-118.56 -11.52  TD -0.067  Tc 1.027  Tw (and that others learn to experience His love through us. David suffers from the fact that he is alone. The ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0472  Tc 0.4872  Tw (devil, also, knows that loneliness is not good for our mental health. So) Tj286.56 0  TD -0.0744  Tc 0.3658  Tw (litary confinement in a prison is one ) Tj-286.56 -11.52  TD -0.068  Tc -0.052  Tw (of the most severe and cruel punishments that can be meted out to a person. ) Tj301.44 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-301.44 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0642  Tc 0.7175  Tw (We cannot say for sure how much David\222s feeling of loneliness is an illusion, or whether he was ) Tj-36 -11.04  TD -0.1139  Tc 1.0739  Tw (really the only godly one left. When Elijah ) Tj179.52 0  TD -0.0741  Tc 0.8033  Tw (thought that he was the only prophet left, God said to him: \223I ) Tj-179.52 -11.52  TD -0.1072  Tc 1.7872  Tw (reserve seven thousand in Israel) Tj132.48 0  TD 0.0034  Tc 0  Tw (--) Tj6.72 0  TD -0.067  Tc 1.2842  Tw ( all whose knees have not bowed down to Baal and all whose mouths ) Tj-139.2 -11.52  TD -0.113  Tc 0.473  Tw (have not kissed him.\224) Tj86.4 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (179) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0386  Tc 0.09  Tw ( But, even if David suffered from an illusion, it was no easier for him) Tj277.92 0  TD -0.0589  Tc -0.0611  Tw ( to bear than if ) Tj-374.4 -11.52  TD -0.0509  Tc 0.1823  Tw (it were reality. The most healthful atmosphere for a person to live in is a fellowship of people who love one ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0737  Tc -0.0463  Tw (another.  ) Tj36.96 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-36.96 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0965  Tc 1.6565  Tw (The faithful are the ones who are part of God\222s covenant with men. The term \223covenant\224 may) Tj0  Tc -0.6  Tw ( ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.1238  Tc 1.6038  Tw (have become discredited be) Tj113.28 0  TD -0.0375  Tc 1.2615  Tw (cause of its use in Calvinistic circles, where it is sometimes used to cover a ) Tj-113.28 -11.52  TD -0.0733  Tc 1.1911  Tw (multitude of sins, when the point is stressed that the covenant is hereditary. But this does not take away ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1015  Tc 2.3815  Tw (anything from the fact that God and man can enter into a covenant that) Tj309.12 0  TD -0.1017  Tc 1.9977  Tw ( is more binding than human) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-309.12 -11.52  TD -0.0906  Tc 3.0906  Tw (marriage vows. William of Orange I declared that he had made a covenant with \223the Potentate of) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0828  Tc 1.2885  Tw (potentates.\224 It is good and healthy for a man to have this kind of relationship with God and to keep the ) TjT* -0.0431  Tc -0.0769  Tw (terms of the contract.) Tj84.48 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-84.48 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.2648  Tc 0.1448  Tw (The ) Tj17.76 0  TD -0.0823  Tc 0.3823  Tw (people in David\222s psalm, either never entered into this covenant relation with God, or they did ) Tj-53.76 -11.52  TD -0.0869  Tc 0.6526  Tw (not keep the terms of it. They were, probably, Israelites to whom the Word of God had come, but who did ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0911  Tc -0.0289  Tw (not consider themselves to be bound by it. This is evide) Tj218.88 0  TD -0.0425  Tc -0.0775  Tw (nt from their relationship with their fellowmen. ) Tj190.56 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-409.44 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0708  Tc 1.6842  Tw (David mentions the tongue, 