wer to our question has to be found in an analogy also. Most of the ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0263  Tc 1.3463  Tw (time sleep is not a con) Tj95.52 0  TD -0.046  Tc 0.8517  Tw (dition we can manipulate according to our own desire. It is sometimes possible to ) Tj-95.52 -11.52  TD -0.0861  Tc 0.4461  Tw (stay awake by an act of the will, but more often than not, sleep is stronger than we are. If we learn to relax, ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0756  Tc 0.6756  Tw (we will fall asleep more easily. In the spiritual realm things) Tj241.44 0  TD -0.0945  Tc 0.4545  Tw ( work in the same way; we can let ourselves go ) Tj-241.44 -11.52  TD -0.0276  Tc -0.001  Tw (to the point of falling asleep, but our determination not to fall asleep will have little or no effect, unless God ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0892  Tc 0.424  Tw (gives light to our eyes. That is why the Bible links watching to prayer. It is the tactic of t) Tj356.64 0  TD -0.0586  Tc -0.0614  Tw (he enemy to lull us ) Tj-356.64 -11.52  TD -0.0282  Tc -0.0918  Tw (to sleep. This realization ought to be enough to jolt us awake, but it, usually, is not. ) Tj333.6 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-297.6 -11.52  TD -0.0679  Tc 0.3774  Tw (The Bible gives us examples of people who fell asleep but who were aroused in time, such as Lot. ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0893  Tc 1.1475  Tw (The secret is in our eyes: as long as our eyes ar) Tj197.76 0  TD -0.1012  Tc 0.8612  Tw (e fixed upon Jesus and we keep on seeing His reality, we ) Tj-197.76 -11.52  TD -0.0991  Tc 0.4363  Tw (will not be overwhelmed by sleep.  Moses kept his eyes on \223Him who is invisible\224 and this saved him from ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1093  Tc 0.9493  Tw (being drugged by the atmosphere of the Egyptian court. The writer to the Hebrews says: \223By fai) Tj392.64 0  TD -0.0851  Tc 0.4451  Tw (th Moses, ) Tj-392.64 -11.52  TD -0.0769  Tc 0.8929  Tw (when he had grown up, refused to be known as the son of Pharaoh\222s daughter. He chose to be mistreated ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0