edicts their ) Tj329.28 0  TD -0.0493  Tc 0.6493  Tw (terror and destruction, he ) Tj-329.28 -11.52  TD -0.0641  Tc 0.3736  Tw (consoles himself with the prospect of a speedy return from his exile; and hopes soon to witness the reunion ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.102  Tc -0.018  Tw (of the tribes of Israel and Judah. It may be applied to unbelievers in general.\224 ) Tj305.28 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-305.28 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0951  Tc 0.8665  Tw (Since the content of this psalm \223may b) Tj157.92 0  TD -0.075  Tc 0.435  Tw (e applied to unbelievers in general,\224 there does not seem to ) Tj-193.92 -11.52  TD -0.0526  Tc 0.6286  Tw (be sufficient reason, however, to presume that it was not written by David, but that it would belong to the ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0995  Tc 1.2718  Tw (period of the Babylonian captivity or thereafter. There were fools in David\222s days. The) Tj358.08 0  TD -0.0408  Tc 0.6408  Tw ( Hebrew word for ) Tj-358.08 -11.52  TD 0.0308  Tc 0.8092  Tw (\223fool\224 is ) Tj40.8 0  TD /F2 10.08  Tf0.2076  Tc 0  Tw (nabal) Tj24 0  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0857  Tc 1.5124  Tw (, and some people in David\222s lifetime were called Nabal.) Tj238.08 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (198) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.12  Tw ( ) Tj3.84 0  TD /F2 10.08  Tf0.0757  Tc 1.2443  Tw (Strong\222s Dictionary) Tj83.04 0  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.113  Tc 0.713  Tw ( defines ) Tj-399.84 -11.52  TD /F2 10.08  Tf0.2076  Tc 0  Tw (nabal) Tj24 0  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0891  Tc -0.0309  Tw ( as \223stupid; wicked \(especially impious\).\224) Tj164.64 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-188.64 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.1055  Tc 0.5503  Tw (The evangelist D. L. Moody was once handed a slip of paper just before he entered the pul) Tj365.28 0  TD -0.1427  Tc 0.2627  Tw (pit. The ) Tj-401.28 -11.52  TD -0.0889  Tc 0.4489  Tw (note had only the word \223fool\224 written on it. Moody read the note aloud and then commented: \223I have heard ) Tj0 -11.52  TD 