Tw (ways, but it sounds the same. The Hebrew says: \223I said to Yahweh: \221you are my Adonai.\222 \224 In the use of ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0769  Tc 0.9169  Tw (these words David expresses God\222s right to rule the life of men. YHWH) Tj297.6 0  TD -0.1848  Tc 0.8328  Tw (, that is the I AM WHO I AM, is ) Tj-297.6 -11.52  TD -0.0611  Tc 0.5651  Tw (the Lord, the Master. This confession is the foundation of the joy of fellowship, which is the theme of this ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0385  Tc 0.6625  Tw (psalm. This confession is not forced out of David, it is voluntary. God does not impose His will upon us; ) TjT* -0.0106  Tc 1.0906  Tw (but if we) Tj37.92 0  TD -0.0445  Tc 0.8409  Tw ( give ourselves to God so that He can do with us what He wants, He will give Himself to us in ) Tj-37.92 -11.52  TD -0.0273  Tc -0.0927  Tw (return. ) Tj28.8 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj7.2 -11.04  TD -0.0737  Tc 0.5095  Tw (\223You are my Lord; apart from you I have no good thing,\224 is one of the most delightful statements ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0708  Tc 0.7799  Tw (in the Bible. It speaks, first of all of possession; \223I ) Tj210.72 0  TD -0.1086  Tc 0.7886  Tw (have\224 expresses possession. The miracle is that a man, ) Tj-210.72 -11.52  TD -0.0687  Tc 0.2519  Tw (who gives all to God, discovers that he possesses all. This is satisfaction to the highest degree. Elsewhere in ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1276  Tc 0.0076  Tw (the psalms the poet says: \223Whom have I in heaven but you? And earth has nothing I desire ) Tj356.64 0  TD -0.1159  Tc -0.0041  Tw (besides you.\224) Tj52.8 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (218) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-383.52 -11.52  TD -0.0805  Tc 0.7184  Tw (The book of Ecclesiastes tells us several times that it is only by God\222s grace that we enjoy things ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0901  Tc 0.8864  Tw (on earth. \223A man can do nothing better than to eat and drink and find satisfaction in his work. This too, I ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0