ith your wives, and ) Tj-144.96 -11.52  TD -0.0635  Tc 1.5435  Tw (treat them with respect as the weaker partner and as heirs with you of the gracious gift of life, so that ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.102  Tc 0.462  Tw (nothing will hinder your prayers.\224) Tj135.84 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (236) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0459  Tc 0.4059  Tw ( The apostle John also speaks about condition) Tj184.8 0  TD -0.0551  Tc 0.3351  Tw (s in which \223our hearts do ) Tj-330.72 -11.52  TD -0.0742  Tc 1.1978  Tw (not condemn us.\224 He says: \223This then is how we know that we belong to the truth, and how we set our ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0778  Tc 0.9418  Tw (hearts at rest in his presence whenever our hearts condemn us. For God is greater than our hearts, and he ) TjT* -0.1368  Tc 2.0968  Tw (knows everything. Dear ) Tj1.9234  Tc 0  Tw (f) Tj105.6 0  TD -0.0761  Tc 1.7389  Tw (riends, if our hearts do not condemn us, we have confidence before God and ) Tj-105.6 -11.52  TD -0.1228  Tc 1.7308  Tw (receive from him anything we ask, because we obey his commands and do what pleases him.\224) Tj395.04 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (237) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.2062  Tc 0.8062  Tw ( These ) Tj-405.12 -11.52  TD -0.0838  Tc -0.0362  Tw (New Testament quotes are, probably, the best illustration of what David is saying her) Tj336.48 0  TD -0.1378  Tc 0.0178  Tw (e. ) Tj9.12 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-345.6 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0744  Tc 1.4972  Tw (There is some value in what is professionally called, \223psychological feelings of guilt,\224 because ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.1279  Tc 0.5505  Tw (they may be the means by which we are drawn to God. What John says is that there comes a point at which ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0545  Tc 0.4145  Tw (we have to cast our burdens upon God, regardless o) Tj209.28 0  TD -0.0536  Tc 0.0936  Tw (f what our heart says. But David does not speak of guilt ) Tj-209.28 -15.36  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw (               