 who passed through \223the Valley of ) Tj-271.68 -11.52  TD -0.0845  Tc 0.5099  Tw (Baca\224 and who make it into a place of springs, because they dwell in the house of the Lord. Here the order ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0541  Tc 0.9181  Tw (is reversed: the trail of goodness and love leads to the house of the Lord. Both directions are correct and ) TjT* -0.1059  Tc 0  Tw (the) Tj12 0  TD -0.0821  Tc 1.3803  Tw (y are both needed. On the road to the house of the Lord the traffic goes two ways. The point is that ) Tj-12 -11.52  TD -0.0691  Tc 0.2775  Tw (goodness and love can never be separated from fellowship with God. It is not ours, but God\222s goodness and ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0614  Tc 2.7014  Tw (love, which stream through us. The stream would ) Tj2.4034  Tc 0  Tw (r) Tj224.16 0  TD -0.0836  Tc 2.3636  Tw (un dry immediately if fellowship with God were) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-224.16 -11.52  TD -0.0559  Tc -0.0641  Tw (interrupted. ) Tj48.48 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-48.48 -11.04  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0965  Tc 0.7091  Tw (Finally, only the priests dwell in the house of the LORD forever. That is why every Christian is a ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0159  Tc 2.2059  Tw (priest. Our task is to perform the duties of our priesthood. Fellowship with God is no vacation) Tj411.84 0  TD -0.2237  Tc 1.0637  Tw (. We ) Tj-411.84 -11.52  TD -0.0772  Tc 0.9172  Tw (constantly carry the burdens of the world in which we live before God. On the basis of Christ\222s sacrifice, ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0525  Tc 1.6548  Tw (we have to intercede without interruption for those with whom we come in contact. Aaron carried the ) TjT* -0.0791  Tc 1.6991  Tw (names of the twelve tribes of Israel upon hi) Tj185.28 0  TD -0.0962  Tc 1.2962  Tw (s shoulders and on his heart, and so he appeared before the ) Tj-185.28 -11.52  TD -0.0653  Tc 0.5453  Tw (Lord. We cannot have fellowship with God without a prayer list on which we write the names of those for ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0915  Tc -0.0285  Tw (whom we pray regularly. This is the secret of the goodness, love, and blessing that trails o) Tj354.72 0  TD -0.0247  Tc -0.0953  Tw (ur lives. ) Tj34.56 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-353.28 -11.52  TD -0.0685  Tc 1.0045  Tw (Dwelling in the house of the Lord also involves living a life of praising God. As we read in the ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0966  Tc 0.6666  Tw (psalm already quoted above: \223Blessed are those who dwell in your house; they are ever praising you.\224) Tj412.8 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (443) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.2366  Tc 0.3566  Tw ( If ) Tj-422.88 -11.52  TD -0.1174  Tc 1.9174  Tw (we can really praise and worship God we hav) Tj193.92 0  TD -0.0897  Tc 1.3297  Tw (e discovered the secret of a life of blessing, and we have ) Tj-193.92 -11.52  TD -0.0482  Tc -0.0718  Tw (opened the source of blessing for others. ) Tj163.2 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-163.2 -372  TD (                              ) Tj72 0  TD (                              ) TjET89.76 88.32 144 0.48 re fBT234.24 85.92  TD( ) Tj-144 -7.2  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tw (443) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf0.1075  Tc -0.2275  Tw ( Ps. 84:4) Tj35.52 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) TjETendstreamendobj374 0 obj5222 endobj375 0 obj<< /Type /Page /Parent 376 0 R /Resources << /Font << /F0 6 0 R /F1 8 0 R /F2 12 0 R /F4 22 0 R >> /ProcSet 2 0 R >> /Contents 377 0 R >> endobj376 0 obj<< /Kids [ 375 0 R 379 0 R 382 0 R 385 0 R 388 0 R 391 0 R ] /Count 6 /Type /Pages /Parent 707 0 R >> endobj377 0 obj<< /Length 378 0 R >> stream
