 Tc -0.1396  Tw (5   Commit your way to the LORD; trust in him and he will do this:) Tj277.44 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-277.44 -11.52  TD 0.0052  Tc -0.1252  Tw (6   He will make your righteousness shine like the dawn, the justice of your c) Tj316.8 0  TD 0.0555  Tc -0.1755  Tw (ause like the noonday sun.) Tj110.88 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-427.68 -11.52  TD 0.0133  Tc 0.7831  Tw (7   Be still before the LORD and wait patiently for him; do not fret when men succeed in their ways, ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0172  Tc -0.1028  Tw (when they carry out their wicked schemes.) Tj174.24 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-174.24 -11.04  TD 0.0253  Tc -0.1453  Tw (8   Refrain from anger and turn from wrath; do not fret) Tj230.4 0  TD 0.0034  Tc 0  Tw (--) Tj6.72 0  TD -0.0069  Tc -0.1131  Tw ( it leads only to evil.) Tj81.6 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-318.72 -11.52  TD 0.1183  Tc -0.2383  Tw (9   F) Tj18.72 0  TD 0.0225  Tc -0.1425  Tw (or evil men will be cut off, but those who hope in the LORD will inherit the land.) Tj333.6 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-352.32 -11.52  TD 0.0227  Tc -0.1427  Tw (10  A little while, and the wicked will be no more; though you look for them, they will not be found.) Tj409.92 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-409.92 -11.52  TD 0.0493  Tc -0.1693  Tw (11  But the meek will inherit the land and enjoy great peace.) Tj251.04 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-251.04 -11.52  TD 0.093  Tc -0.213  Tw (12  The w) Tj40.8 0  TD 0.061  Tc -0.181  Tw (icked plot against the righteous and gnash their teeth at them;) Tj259.68 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-300.48 -11.52  TD 0.0485  Tc -0.1685  Tw (13  but the Lord laughs at the wicked, for he knows their day is coming.) Tj297.6 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-297.6 -11.52  TD 0.0313  Tc 0.0544  Tw (14 The wicked draw the sword and bend the bow to bring down the poor and needy, to slay those whose ) Tj0 -11.52  TD 0.0499  Tc -0.1699  Tw (ways are upright.) Tj72.48 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-72.48 -11.52  TD 0.24  Tc 0  Tw (1) Tj5.28 0  TD 0.0274  Tc -0.1474  Tw (5  But their swords will pierce their own hearts, and their bows will be broken.) Tj323.52 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-328.8 -11.52  TD 0.0413  Tc -0.1613  Tw (16  Better the little that the righteous have than the wealth of many wicked;) Tj313.44 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-313.44 -11.52  TD 0.0234  Tc -0.1434  Tw (17  for the power of the wicked will be broken, but the LORD upholds the righteous.) Tj348 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-348 -11.52  TD 0.0894  Tc -0.2094  Tw (18  The days ) Tj55.2 0  TD 0.0054  Tc -0.1254  Tw (of the blameless are known to the LORD, and their inheritance will endure forever.) Tj344.64 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-399.84 -11.52  TD 0.0125  Tc -0.1325  Tw (19  In times of disaster they will not wither; in days of famine they will enjoy plenty.) Tj346.08 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-346.08 -11.52  TD 0.0284  Tc -0.2331  Tw (20  But the wicked will perish: The LORD's enemies will be like the beauty of the fi) Tj343.68 0  TD 0.0266  Tc -0.6266  Tw (elds, they will vanish) Tj84.96 0  TD 0.0034  Tc 0  Tw (-) Tj-428.64 -11.52  TD (-) Tj3.36 0  TD 0.0071  Tc -0.1271  Tw ( vanish like smoke.) Tj78.72 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-82.08 -11.52  TD 0.024  Tc -0.144  Tw (21  The wicked borrow and do not repay, but the righteous give generously;) Tj312.96 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-312.96 -11.52  TD 0.0156  Tc -0.1356  Tw (22  those the LORD blesses will inherit the land, but those he curses will be cut off.) Tj343.2 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-343.2 -11.52  TD 0.0468  Tc -0.1668  Tw (23  If the LORD delights in a man's way, he makes ) Tj214.56 0  TD -0  Tc -0.1195  Tw (his steps firm;) Tj58.56 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-273.12 -11.52  TD 0.0542  Tc -0.1742  Tw (24  though he stumble, he will not fall, for the LORD upholds him with his hand.) Tj337.44 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-337.44 -11.52  TD 0.0213  Tc -0.2286  Tw (25  I was young and now I am old, yet I have never seen the righteous forsaken or their children begging ) Tj0 -11.52  TD 0.1406  Tc 0  Tw (bread.) Tj26.4 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-26.4 -11.52  TD 0.0298  Tc -0.1498  Tw (26  They are always generous and lend freely; t) Tj196.32 0  TD 0.0412  Tc -0.1612  Tw (heir children will be blessed.) Tj118.56 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-314.88 -11.52  TD 0.0227  Tc -0.1427  Tw (27  Turn from evil and do good; then you will dwell in the land forever.) Tj295.2 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-295.2 -11.04  TD 0.0033  Tc -0.1462  Tw (28  For the LORD loves the just and will not forsake his faithful ones. They will be protected forever, but ) Tj0 -11.52  TD 0.0178  Tc -0.1378  Tw (the offspring of the wicked will be cut off;) Tj173.28 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-173.28 -11.52  TD 0.0444  Tc -0.1644  Tw (29  the righteous will inherit the land and dwell in it forever.) Tj251.52 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-251.52 -11.52  TD 0.0359  Tc -0.1559  Tw (30  The mouth of the righteous man utters wisdom, and his tongue speaks what is just.) Tj359.04 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-359.04 -11.52  TD 0.0419  Tc -0.1619  Tw (31  The law of his God is in his heart; his feet do not slip.) Tj237.12 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-237.12 -11.52  TD 0.0383  Tc -0.1583  Tw (32  The wicked lie in wait for the righteo) Tj168.48 0  TD -0.0172  Tc -0.1028  Tw (us, seeking their very lives;) Tj111.36 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-279.84 -11.52  TD 0.018  Tc -0.138  Tw (33  but the LORD will not leave them in their power or let them be condemned when brought to trial.) Tj417.12 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-417.12 -11.52  TD 0.041  Tc 0.0268  Tw (34  Wait for the LORD and keep his way. He will exalt you to inherit the land; when the wicked are cut ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0424  Tc -0.0776  Tw (off, you will see it.) Tj74.4 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-74.4 -11.52  TD 0.24  Tc 0  Tw (3) Tj5.28 0  TD 0.0333  Tc -0.1533  Tw (5  I have seen a wicked and ruthless man flourishing like a green tree in its native soil,) Tj359.52 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-364.8 -11.52  TD 0.0304  Tc -0.1504  Tw (36  but he soon passed away and was no more; though I looked for him, he could not be found.) Tj393.6 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-393.6 -11.52  TD 0.0112  Tc -0.1312  Tw (37  Consider the blameless, observe the upright; there is a future for t) Tj287.52 0  TD -0.0085  Tc -0.1115  Tw (he man of peace.) Tj70.08 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-357.6 -11.52  TD 0.0228  Tc -0.1428  Tw (38  But all sinners will be destroyed; the future of the wicked will be cut off.) Tj313.44 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-313.44 -11.52  TD -0.002  Tc -0.118  Tw (39  The salvation of the righteous comes from the LORD; he is their stronghold in time of trouble.) Tj405.12 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-405.12 -11.52  TD 0.0133  Tc 0.0412  Tw (40  The LORD helps them and delivers them; he delivers them) Tj259.68 0  TD 0.0038  Tc -0.1238  Tw ( from the wicked and saves them, because ) Tj-259.68 -11.52  TD 0.0258  Tc -0.1458  Tw (they take refuge in him.) Tj98.88 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-98.88 -11.52  TD /F0 10.08  Tf( ) Tj0 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.1038  Tc 0.8104  Tw (The theme of this psalm is, obviously, \223dwell in the land.\224 This phrase, and \223inherit the land\224 are ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0716  Tc 1.3916  Tw (found at least seven times in this psalm.) Tj167.52 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (694) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.192  Tc 1.032  Tw ( In his ) Tj30.72 0  TD /F2 10.08  Tf0.0247  Tc 0  Tw (Commentary) Tj52.32 0  TD /F0 10.08  Tf0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj3.84 0  TD /F2 10.08  Tf0.0728  Tc 1.2472  Tw (on the Psalms) Tj60 0  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.1021  Tc 0.9421  Tw (, George Knigh) Tj62.88 0  TD -0.0727  Tc 0.5927  Tw (t gives this ) Tj-387.36 -15.36  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw (                              ) Tj72 0  TD (                              ) TjET89.76 88.32 144 0.48 re fBT234.24 85.92  TD( ) Tj-144 -7.2  TD /F0 6.72 