f ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1078  Tc -0.0122  Tw (God. David may not express this very clearly here, but this is his intent. ) Tj283.2 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-283.2 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.1061  Tc 1.9061  Tw (David expects an answer fro) Tj119.52 0  TD -0.0447  Tc 1.6601  Tw (m God, not only an answer to his questions, but that God would ) Tj-155.52 -11.52  TD -0.0703  Tc 1.177  Tw (answer his enemies. God\222s answers are often quite different from what we expect. God is always full of ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0501  Tc 1.4266  Tw (surprises. In the book of Job, Job puts a series of questions before God, to which he rece) Tj375.84 0  TD -0.0659  Tc 0.9059  Tw (ives no direct ) Tj-375.84 -11.52  TD -0.0727  Tc 0.4861  Tw (answer. When God appears to Job, He speaks about things that were quite different from the questions that ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0726  Tc 0.7432  Tw (occupied Job\222s mind. Yet, we get the impression that Job considered that all his questions were answered. ) TjT* -0.0421  Tc 1.3621  Tw (It appears that God answers t) Tj121.44 0  TD -0.0852  Tc 1.1172  Tw (he questions we ought to have asked, which are not always the ones we do ) Tj-121.44 -11.04  TD -0.0789  Tc 0.4846  Tw (ask. We often ask the wrong questions, or we do not know what to ask. Seeing God and walking with Him ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0573  Tc 0.2802  Tw (will make most of our questions melt away. \223The things of earth will grow strange) Tj332.16 0  TD -0.0786  Tc -0.0414  Tw (ly dim, in the light of His ) Tj-332.16 -11.52  TD -0.0996  Tc 0.7567  Tw (glory and grace.\224 God answers us in Jesus Christ. He does not give an answer; He is the answer. Once we ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1018  Tc 0.5338  Tw (have learned to ask the right questions, we have become mature. This is what C. S. Lewis means to convey ) TjT* -0.0451  Tc 0.2451  Tw (in his book ) Tj48 0  TD /F2 10.08  Tf-0  Tc 0.3606  Tw (Till We) Tj29.76 0  TD -0.0244  Tc 0.3844  Tw ( Have Faces) Tj50.88 0  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0581  Tc 0.3914  Tw (. One of the main purposes of our being on earth is that we learn to ask the ) Tj-128.64 -11.52  TD -0.056  Tc 0.2644  Tw (right questions. The problem is never that God does not know the answers to our questions. The question is ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0957  Tc 0.6157  Tw (not what is being said, either by God or by us. God\222s answers) Tj249.6 0  TD -0.0609  Tc 0.3676  Tw ( to David stopped the mouths of his enemies. ) Tj-249.6 -11.52  TD -0.0726  Tc 1.3361  Tw (God\222s answer is always creative; to David it comes in the form of salvation, healing, and rehabilitation. ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0931  Tc -0.0269  Tw (God\222s answer to David would completely change the relationship between him and his enemies. ) Tj381.6 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-381.6 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.151  Tc 1.471  Tw (In this psa) Tj42.72 0  TD -0.0786  Tc 0.9186  Tw (lm, David experiences a tremendous spiritual struggle. Demons are stronger than men. ) Tj-78.72 -11.52  TD -0.0781  Tc 0.5752  Tw (The battle is unmatched, if we are left to ourselves. The devil always wants us to believe that we are alone ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1017  Tc 1.1599  Tw (when we face him. That is the crisis David passes through here) Tj260.64 0  TD -0.0734  Tc 0.8068  Tw (; but pass through he does, because of his ) Tj-260.64 -11.52  TD -0.0734  Tc 0.3191  Tw (trust in the Lord. He has visions of what could happen to him, and that makes him afraid. But the assurance ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0477  Tc 0.4344  Tw (that God will not forsake him settles the matter. He also understands that the wall of opposition he face) Tj418.56 0  TD -0.0282  Tc 0.1482  Tw (s is ) Tj-418.56 -11.52  TD -0.0677  Tc 0.5191  Tw (the result of pursuing what is good. In a sense, it is always encouraging when the devil takes the trouble to ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0577  Tc -0.0623  Tw (make life hard for us; it is an indication that he considers us to be a threat to him. ) Tj323.04 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-323.04 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0984  Tc 1.0694  Tw (The prayer: \223Be not far from me, O my God. Come quic) Tj234.24 0  TD -0.0807  Tc 0.814  Tw (kly to help me,\224 is a strange mixture of ) Tj-270.24 -11.52  TD -0.1039  Tc 0.4013  Tw (hope and doubt. That is the way we are as human beings, and God does not seem to mind this. The fact that ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0559  Tc 2.5759  Tw (God would be far from us, and that He would have to hurry to help us is anthropomorphism. The) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) TjT* -0.0338  Tc 2.3138  Tw (omnipresent God) Tj71.04 0  TD -0.1036  Tc 2.0636  Tw ( is never far, and \223come quickly\224 is a time) Tj184.32 0  TD 0.0034  Tc 0  Tw (-) Tj3.36 0  TD -0.0771  Tc 1.6371  Tw (bound concept that does not apply to the ) Tj-258.72 -11.52  TD -0.0677  Tc 0.3477  Tw (Eternal One. The paradox finds its basis in our humanity. The Apostle Paul illustrates this beautifully in his ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0896  Tc 0.8336  Tw (address to the philosophers at the Areopagus, when he said: ) Tj247.2 0  TD -0.1083  Tc 0.415  Tw (\223From one man he made every nation of men, ) Tj-247.2 -11.52  TD -0.1028  Tc 1.5743  Tw (that they should inhabit the whole earth; and he determined the times set for them and the exact places ) Tj0 -11.04  TD -0.0857  Tc 0.9486  Tw (where they should live. God did this so that men would seek him and perhaps reach out for him and find ) Tj0 -11.52  TD 0.1187  Tc 0.7213  Tw (him, t) Tj24 0  TD -0.0425  Tc 0.8825  Tw (hough he is not far from each one of us.\224) Tj171.36 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (742) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0577  Tc 0.7377  Tw ( \223He is not far from each one of us,\224 but we can be far ) Tj-205.44 -11.52  TD -0.078  Tc 1.4232  Tw (from Him, spiritually, and emotionally. Two people can sit next to each other and be miles apart at the ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0872  Tc 0.9272  Tw (same time. It is up to us to approach God. This may be) Tj227.04 0  TD -0.0504  Tc 0.5849  Tw ( 